@Node "Disclaimer" "ViewMagic.guide/Disclaimer"
@Next "Copying"
@Prev "Main"
@TOC  "Main"

                             @{B}Disclaimer@{UB}


This is ViewMagic's first ever release.  Absolutely no responsibility 
is taken by the author.  This program is provided AS IS.

Please, as this is the first wide release, try it out with unimportant 
data until such time that you are sure of ViewMagic's capabilities. 
ViewMagic has been in use on different machines, but there is always 
the possibility of conflict.  No claims are made for reliability or 
accuracy.

ViewMagic has been tested on an A4000 with WB3.0, an A3000 with WB3.1, 
an A1200 with WB3.0, as well as on an A2000 with WB2.1.  CPUs covered 
in these tests are '040s, '030s and 68000s.

"Magic: the Gathering" is a trademark of Wizards of the Coast.
All card information is also copyrighted by Wizards of the Coast.

It is also not promised that the data contained in the Master list
is 100% accurate.  Typing errors and conversion errors probably have
crept in somewhere.  If you find some please report errors 
to @{" Scot Lemieux " Link "ScotLemieux"}.

If a reproducible bug is found, please do not hesitate to inform 
anyone related to ViewMagic, such as @{" Scot Lemieux " Link "ScotLemieux"}.

@EndNode

