Persons wishing to include this program on a "cover disk", CD-ROM, or
anywhere else should contact @{" Scot Lemieux " Link "ScotLemieux"} first.

@EndNode

@Node "Introduction" "ViewMagic.guide/Introduction"
@Next "Requirements"
@Prev "Copying"
@TOC  "Main"

                           @{B}Introduction@{UB}


ViewMagic was written out of need, since there was nothing available
on the Amiga to quickly and easily keep track of MtG cards. I was 
getting tired of trying to keep track of what I owned on paper.

The program has gone through only a couple of revisions at this point 
considering it was a simple program to write.  The hardest part was
gathering the card data and compiling it into a usable format.

This program sees a great deal of use in my circle of MtG friends who 
have Amigas and is appreciated.  It has been made available to all 
so that many can make use of it.  I use the equivalent of registered 
version of course because of its additional components such as
deck creation, additional artist information, and pricing scales.

See @{" Registering " Link "Registering"} about getting this version for yourself.

@EndNode

@Node "Requirements" "ViewMagic.guide/Requirements"
@Next "Using"
@Prev "Introduction"
@TOC  "Main"

                       @{B}ViewMagic Requirements@{UB}


@{B}The requirements are small:@{UB}

 - WorkBench 2.x and up
 - The card masterlist
 - An Amiga computer
 - and a bit of time to enter all your cards the first time

@EndNode

@Node "Using" "ViewMagic.guide/Using"
@Next "Contributors"
@Prev "Requirements"
@TOC  "Main"

                           @{B}Using ViewMagic@{UB}


ViewMagic can be run from it's Workbench icon or from a command line.  
If you are running it from a CLI/Shell, please make sure your stack 
is at least 180000 bytes, and if you encounter problems with a super 
large list, increase it.  Or if you have memory to spare, make it
200k.  Also ensure that all files included in the archive are in the 
same directory, particularly the ViewMagic program and the master data
file that it must load upon being launched.  Other files can be anywhere.

Find the card in the master list and click on it for every time that
you own it and it will be copied into the user list.  It requires only 
a single click for speed, because when entering 1500 cards, double 
clicking becomes quite frustrating.

The user list can be saved or others can be loaded.

@{B}NOTE:@{UB} In the registered version you can load your personal master list 
into the 'Master List' column, and create decks from your database.

@{B}Options are as follows:@{UB}

@{B}No Confirm@{UB}   > No confirmation of any kind occurs when selecting cards 
                from any list. IE you click on it, it is copied, or 
                deleted quietly.

@{B}Confirm Copy@{UB} > A requester will ask you to confirm a copy each time

@{B}Confirm Del@{UB}  > A requester will ask you to confirm a delete each time

@{B}Confirm Both@{UB} > A requester will confirm either a copy or delete action 
                each time, essentially the same as the above two combined

@{B}Card Info@{UB}    > This will only display the card information and no
                copying of any kind is done at all

When picking options from the cycle gadgets dedicated for card types you 
will find they work like an AND operation.  This was found to be ideal 
when entering a card collection into the program.  With the card specific 
cycle gadgets, one can pick what @{B}Expansion Set@{UB}, what @{B}Rarity level@{UB}, what @{B}Color@{UB} 
and what @{B}Spell Type@{UB} to choose from in the listings.  This greatly reduces 
the number of visible cards in the listings and allows for quicker selection. 

The series of buttons are quite simple, they allow you to load and save 
your card list, as well as choose what font to program uses along with 
which screen is to be used as default.  When one quits the program, the 
@{B}preferences@{UB} ( size, position, font, screen, etc ) are saved in 
the ENVARC: & ENV: directories.

Although the program is quite fast, the amount of information being 
manipulated might cause it to be sluggish on slow if you are trying to 
copy or delete with all cards visible due to listview updating, although 
things are nice when using it with an '040. :)

@EndNode

@Node "Contributors" "ViewMagic.guide/Contributors"
@Next "Registering"
@Prev "Using"
@TOC  "Main"

                            @{B}About the Contributors
                            and how to reach them@{UB}


Programming                     @{" Scot Lemieux              " Link "ScotLemieux"}
Card Data Provider              @{" John Wetmiller            " Link "John"}
Program Support & Distribution  @{" Sean MacPhee              " Link "Sean"}
Merchandise Support             @{" Crescent Moon Enterprises " Link "CME"}
 
If you come across any curiosities, bugs or strange events that 
ViewMagic is responsible for or affected by please let someone involved 
know as soon as you have a chance so that we may offer assistance or a remedy. 

If you find errors in the master list, pertaining to card info please do the
same, and provide a correction if possible.

User feedback is the primary method for improving any program, since there 
are always events that programmers never encounter.

@EndNode

@Node "Registering" "ViewMagic.guide/Registering"
@Next "CME"
@Prev "Contributors"
@TOC  "Main"

                             @{B}Registering@{UB}


ViewMagic v1.0 is Shareware.  If you like it, enjoy it and use it.

On the other hand if you don't like it don't use it. :)

By registering you'll receive a new program that will:

- Allow you to create decks from a selected user list instead of 
    the 'master' list
- Save & Edit more preferences
- Contain artist name(s), card abilities, and card poetry
- Hot Key equivalents for all gadgets
- A configurable list generator which will create a text file 
    in any format to be used to mail or print

You can register by:

  Sending - 15$US for international users or
          - 15$CAN for Canadian users
            in the form of an international money order addressed to
            "Crescent Moon Enterprises" and mail it to:

     @{B} ViewMagic Registration c/o Crescent Moon Enterprises
      5938 Meadowglen Drive
      Orleans, Ontario
      Canada
      K1C 5Z6@{UB}

      Also include your mailing address & E-Mail address.

  Additional info about @{" Crescent Moon Enterprises " Link "CME"}.

You will then receive:
  
  A random booster pack from one of the current MtG expansions
  A registered version of the program via E-Mail
  ( If you wish to have ViewMagic sent to you on a diskette, 
    please indicate so with your registration, add 3$ for a diskette
    and additional postal requirements.  Using 'E-Mail' in some manner
    or another is highly recommened and prefered )

@EndNode

